Thulsie twins back in court. JOHANNESBURG - The Thulsie twins have entered into a plea deal with the state at the 11th hour. Their terrorism trial was to get underway on Monday, six years after they were arrested during raids in Gauteng. READ: Thulsie terrorism case postponed Authorities alleged Brandon-Lee and Tony-Lee Thulsie were part of ISIS. They accuse them of planning to detonate explosives at the US embassy and Jewish institutions in South Africa. The twins' attorney says they have agreed to sign the plea agreement freely. BREAKING: The State and the defense in the Thulsie Twins matter has entered into a plea agreement. It has been signed by all parities. #eNCA